## 2. Initial Jensen Diagnostics

The first finite Jensen scan used

\[
A_k=\frac{M_k k!}{(2k)!}.
\]

The low-degree scan tested:

- degrees \(2,3,4,5,6,8,10\);
- \(n=0,\ldots,20\);
- \(\lambda\in\{0,10^{-6},10^{-5},10^{-4},10^{-3},10^{-2},5\times10^{-2},10^{-1}\}\).

After switching to scaled polynomial coefficients, no mathematical Jensen failures were detected in this range.

### Status

Low-degree finite Jensen evidence passed for all tested \(\lambda\) values.

