- degrees \(2,\ldots,20\);
- \(n=0,\ldots,80\);
- moments up to \(M_{100}\).

The initial floating root scan reported:

- total tests: \(1539\);
- reported failures: \(256\);
- first reported failures at degree \(16\).

Failure count by degree:

| Degree | Reported failures |
|---:|---:|
| 2–15 | 0 |
| 16 | 17 |
| 17 | 37 |
| 18 | 54 |
| 19 | 67 |
| 20 | 81 |

The first reported failure was:

\[
\lambda=0,\qquad d=16,\qquad n=54.
\]

A direct verification was then performed using the printed high-precision coefficients for this case and Sturm/root counting on

\[
Q(y)=P(-y).
\]

Result:

- degree: \(16\);
- positive real roots of \(Q\): \(16\);
- all real roots of \(Q\): \(16\);
- pass: true.

The roots of \(Q(y)\) were all positive real, approximately:

\[
279.37,\ 321.40,\ 359.05,\ 395.01,\ 430.29,\ 465.47,\ 500.94,\ 537.00,
\]

\[
573.96,\ 612.13,\ 651.88,\ 693.73,\ 738.39,\ 787.01,\ 841.83,\ 908.58.
