## 9. Methodological Update

The extended Jensen work shows that high-degree polynomial root classification by floating solvers can produce false nonreal roots due to conditioning.

Future Jensen diagnostics should use:

1. high-precision moment computation;
2. construction of \(Q_{d,n}(y)=P_{d,n}(-y)\);
3. Sturm root counting for positive real roots;
4. floating root solvers only as secondary diagnostics.

The primary finite Jensen pass criterion should be:

\[
\#\{\text{positive real roots of }Q_{d,n}\}=d.
\]

---

## 10. Route Status

The kernel route currently separates into three branches.

### Dead or weak branch

Ordinary log-concavity.

The sampled \(Q_2\) diagnostic does not support naive log-concavity.

### Damaged branch

Simple PF\(_\infty\) Toeplitz coefficient route.

Robust sampled Toeplitz minors are negative.

### Active branch

Finite Jensen hyperbolicity via Sturm verification.

This is currently the strongest kernel-side route.

